<Verbatim PAsource="" >TWO "cowboy" builders who </Verbatim>
<Rewrite PAsource="" >swindled </Rewrite>
<Verbatim PAsource="" >pensioners out of </Verbatim>
<Rewrite PAsource="" >their </Rewrite>
<Verbatim PAsource="" >life savings, leaving </Verbatim>
<Rewrite PAsource="" >one </Rewrite>
<Verbatim PAsource="" >so poor </Verbatim>
<Rewrite PAsource="" >that </Rewrite>
<Verbatim PAsource="" >she had to have her cat </Verbatim>
<Rewrite PAsource="" >destroyed, </Rewrite>
<Verbatim PAsource="" >were jailed </Verbatim>
<Rewrite PAsource="" >yesterday.</Rewrite>


<Verbatim PAsource="" >Robert Sheridan and Thomas Forbes, both 44, </Verbatim>
<Rewrite PAsource="" >using the </Rewrite>
<Verbatim PAsource="" >trading names Dr Guttering and Drips 'R' Us, posed as "master craftsmen" </Verbatim>
<Rewrite PAsource="" >but neither had any </Rewrite>
<Verbatim PAsource="" >building qualifications, Birmingham Crown court </Verbatim>
<Rewrite PAsource="" >was told.</Rewrite>


<Verbatim PAsource="" >The </Verbatim>
<Rewrite PAsource="" >men, </Rewrite>
<Verbatim PAsource="" >both </Verbatim>
<Rewrite PAsource="" >from </Rewrite>
<Verbatim PAsource="" >Walker's Heath Road, Birmingham, tricked their victims out of a total of £45,000.</Verbatim>


<Verbatim PAsource="" >Nicholas Webb, prosecuting, said </Verbatim>
<Rewrite PAsource="" >that </Rewrite>
<Verbatim PAsource="" >Verna Hotchkiss, 69, had been forced to have her 15-year-old cat </Verbatim>
<Rewrite PAsource="" >destroyed </Rewrite>
<Verbatim PAsource="" >because she could not afford vet's fees </Verbatim>
<Rewrite PAsource="" >after </Rewrite>
<Verbatim PAsource="" >she had paid Dr Guttering £4,660 for work worth £200 on her home in Stirchley, Birmingham.</Verbatim>


<Verbatim PAsource="" >The defendants pleaded guilty </Verbatim>
<New PAsource="" >to plotting </New>
<Verbatim PAsource="" >to defraud. </Verbatim>
<Verbatim PAsource="" >Sheridan </Verbatim>
<Rewrite PAsource="" >was jailed </Rewrite>
<Verbatim PAsource="" >for three years and three months </Verbatim>
<Rewrite PAsource="" >and </Rewrite>
<Verbatim PAsource="" >Forbes for four years. </Verbatim>
<Verbatim PAsource="" >Mrs Justice Smith </Verbatim>
<Rewrite PAsource="" >said: </Rewrite>
<Verbatim PAsource="" >"These were despicable offences."</Verbatim>



